@node usage "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Usage..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b} Usage, Short description@{ub}

   As far as you did activate the EASys!-ToolManager, you may now call
   the following functions by Keyboard-Shortcuts:

   Exclusively on Workbench, after clicking onto icon(s):

    RightAmiga  i    @{"   " link EASys!_FM.guide/main} EASys! InfoManager, File-Information
    RightAmiga  o   @{"   " link presentate} EASys! Presenator, Start File/presentate
    RightAmiga  t       EASys! & TTManager, edit ToolTypes
    RightAmiga  x   @{"   " link EASys!_FM.guide/main} EASys! TrashManager, Trashing-Dialogue
    RightAmiga  z   show by Multiview

   Workbench windows and icons:

    RightAmiga l    Show all files
    RightAmiga .    Show only files which have an own icon
    RightAmiga p    Show files as icons
    RightAmiga n    Show files as a list of names

    RightAmiga f    Snapshot all
    RightAmiga s    Snapshot all selected icons

   On all Screens:

    LeftShift Help  @{"   " link EASys!_GlobalHelp.guide/main} EASys! GlobalHelp

    RightShift F4   @{"   " link presentate} EASys! PresentationManager
    RightShift F5   @{"   " link EASys!_FM.guide/main} EASys! FileManager
    RightShift F6   @{"   " link EASys!_FileStarter.guide/main} EASys! StartFile-Manager (Icon-SendTo)

    ATTENTION: Please note, that the WB-Menus have been reconfigured
        to new @{"   " link S:ReKeyIt.menus/main} keyboard shortcuts!

    Especially the EASys! FileManager is suggested to keep only
    called by the given key-combination. It may be called multiply
    without interference. Only the destination pathes of your copy
    and move operations will be globally used in all open FileManagers.

    As to mention the CompressManager, it may also be called 
    multiply without any interference.

    I would like to strongly suggest activating the "PubModes"
    (Shanghai and PopPubScreen) Functionality when using MCP, MultiCX
    or other Commodities so that all EASys!-Requesters will automatically
    appear upon the actually frontmost Screen.

    Thus, from within any Screen, you may quick and easy call the
    EASys!-Wizards just by FingerTip.


    @{b} File Request Windows@{ub}

    The FileRequest Windows supplied by EASys! (ReqTools Requesters)
    may be used in the following way:

     * Drop Workbench- or DOpus Icons upon them.
     * Doubleklick a File in the Requester for selecting it.
     * Select multiple Files just by LeftShift-Klicking onto them
       one after the other. Then ENTER.
     * Select Directories in the way you select multiple files...
     * Select Destination-Directories (when initiating copy or move
       actions), just drag a Workbench drawer into the filerequester.

    So, try this, too, now. Best, if you call the EASys! FileManager
    (RightShift F5). Naturally, this is only possible by function keys,
    if you have an up and running EASys!-Dock!


    @{b} EASys!-Dock@{ub}

    The EASys! Dock App-Buttons are parametrized
    to support multiple functionality:

     * Simple-Klick: A Dialog will be started, which in most cases
       will offer a FileRequester Window for selecting Files.

     * Drag&Drop: Icons may also be dropped upon the App-Buttons.
       The Icons may originate from almost different drawer-Windows
       (which is ONLY possible with AMIGA!). Here, the number of dropped
       items is limited by the maximum AmigaDOS commandline-length.
       Assuming, that each Icon represents it's whole FileSystemPath,
       in most cases, at least 15 Files should be processable. If nothing
       happens after dropping files, the length has been exceeded. Just
       call the EASys!-Wizard by Simple-Klick then, supplying an
       unlimited selectable FileRequest.

     Go, and try that now! Best to first-use with the Editor App-Button
     (Button Nr. 5 from the left).


____________________________________________________________________
@endnode



@node shell "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Shell-Enhancements"
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________



   @{b}Additional Shell-Functionality!@{ub}

   From now on, you may also use some short calls for some
   EASys! wizards within EASys!_bin:  Where listed, there
   exists the possibility of commandline argument passing
   (the options will be explained if you call the utility
   by one argument: "??").

   @{"   " link EASys!_bin:english/sText.help/main} sText    Options    Textketten in Dateien suchen
   @{"   " link EASys!_bin:english/rText.help/main} rText    Options    Textketten in Dateien ersetzen
   @{"   " link EASys!_bin:english/man.help/main} man      Option     The EASys! GlobalHelp
   @{"   " link EASys!_bin:english/fm.help/main} fm       Dir-Option The EASys! FileManager
   @{"   " link EASys!_bin:english/cm.help/main} cm                  The EASys! CompressManager



   After once having rebooted your AMIGA, the shell will offer
   various new and very usable aliases:


   * For better use of @{"   " link aminetcds} Aminet-CDs:

     Instead of calling the configurable but far not flexible enough
     hard coded Aminet-CD Viewer, upon now, the EASys!-Presentation-
     Manager will be called directly when clicking a Aminet-CD's
     Guide-Button (fully transparent usage).


   * For Developers and engineers:

     dechex, hexdec, decoct, decbin, bindec
     for converting constants from one type to another
     (e.g.: dechex 21   will convert 21 decimal to it's hex equivalent)


   * For further info, consult the ModAS ©TNE Shell-PreConfigurator:

     @{"   " link SYS:StartSys/b_GUI/7_StartShell/main} SYS:StartSys/b_GUI/7_StartShell

____________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node featurenotes "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: features"
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________



   @{b}EASys! becomes  EASys! @{ub}

                  @{b}E@{ub} rgonomic
                  @{b}A@{ub} llover
                  @{b}Sys@{ub} tem enhancer !


   @{b}Characteristics@{ub}


   * Universal philosophy und unified user interface

   * High functionality and integration of third-party-products

   * High flexibility in customizing



   * The Standard WB finally gets the extension which it
     should have deserved long ago. Fully integrated by
     ToolManager-Menu and Keyboard-Shortcuts. Fully integrated
     @{"   " link EASys!_GloalHelp.guide/main} System-GlobalHelp included.

   * Icon-Links for Programs and Multimedia-Files that are
     located on not actually mounted devices (such as CDROMS)
     may be easily created in any desired direcotry
     on Harddisk.

   * Just by "FingerTip" the "On the Fly" EASys!-FileManager
     will be at your disposal in every Application. Comfortable
     File-Duplicates-Information when copying or moving Files.

   * Shell- or Commandline Inputs will from now on only be
     necessary in special situations (e.g.: Develpment).

   * The EASys! FileManager may be second only by other
     FileManagers (RO, DirWork, ...) if huge File-Copy or
     -Move Operations are to be scheduled.


____________________________________________________________________


  @{"   " link EASys!_news/main}   New Features


  @{b}@{u}Features@{uu}:@{ub}

  * Fully @{b}dialog-based@{ub} and @{b}!(yet german-)talking!@{ub}
    User-Interface assistants.

  * @{b}A corporately designed intuitive@{ub} System-to-User interface,

    providing basic system functions,
    System maintenance functions and
    MultiMedia related functionality

  * The innovative @{"   " link EASys!_References.guide/main} @{b}SysDatabase@{ub}:
    Fully customizable to each user's System-Directory-Environment.
    Center configuration of many application's and all script's parameters.



  @{b}@{u}Release Notes@{uu}@{ub}

  (first release: 3.0)
  Completely german and english localized package.
  Will switch it's language and voice following the LocalePrefs.
  Translation to other languages easily by applying translated
  Message-Files in

     EASys!_rexx:<Language is deutsch,english ...>

  Sorry, for the first release, there will only be german voice
  samples available. Nevertheless, EASys! will be fully functional.
  New samples may be added to:

     Locale:Voice/<Language is deutsch,english ...>

  Rexx-script based installation procedure embedded with
  AmigaGuide. An uninstall script will automatically be generated
  with the installation. It may be called by Icon after
  finishing the installation.


  @{b}@{u}Based upon@{uu}:@{ub}

  AMIGA REXX Inter-Process Communications, the most unique
  Amiga-Feature.

  RexxReqTools Library Package

  Several  util/cli   Utilities, available on AmiNet /
  supplied with EASys!

  Several commercial and non-commercial Applications available for
  the AMIGA (your task to purchase and supply!)

____________________________________________________________________
@endnode



@node philosophy "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Philosophy..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}@{u}Philosophy@{uu} ...@{ub}

   One goal was to deliver a @{b}complete package@{ub}.
   Thus it has grown very, very big.

   But you will be free of entering the aminet, searching and
   collecting all numberous additional CLI-Binaries. So, this should
   be really user-friendly for you to install.

   @{"   " link EASys!_References.guide/main} SysDatabase:
   Center configuration of parameters for the whole system,
   all scripts and many application's configuration files.

   Another goal was, to provide an installation procedure that is started
   out of the AmigaGuide and NOT based on the installer but based on ARexx.

   So, no one will have to click around with those ugly
   Installer-File-Requests. We're all familiar with RexxReqTools or ASL.
   Why did they invent another "wheel" of browsing for the installer ???

   Now and here's the EASys! Rexx Installer.
   The EASys!-installation is managed thereby.

____________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node enhance "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Applications..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}@{u}Where to use it@{uu} ...@{ub}

   Daily work with the AMIGA, calling the wizards by Function-Keys
               or ToolManager Docks or StartMenu-startups ...
               quite everywhere you might imagine those Wizards
               may help you, everywhere you are able to include
               Shell- or Arexx-Scripts.


   @{"   " link EASys!_environment.guide/main} @{b}General tips for the EASys! System environment@{ub}

   plugin-usage inside other applications such as

   GoldEd  ©1998 Dietmar Eilert
           ShareWare text-editor
           IMHO the most advanced at the moment
   CygnusEd ©1990 CygnusSoft
           commercial text-editor
           IMHO one of the best.
           Development will be continued by Schatztruhe '97.
   IBrowse ©1996 Omnipresence Int.
           commercial WWW-Browser, MUI-based
           IMHO the most advanced and comfortable Browser for
           the AMIGA. MUI is a phantastic GUI enhancement for the
           AMIGA and is © by Stefan Stuntz.

   PictureManager ©1996 IrseeSoft
           commercial Image-Works and cataloging software
           IMHO not the fastest but a very powerful package
   ScreenTab 3.2 © 1998 Michael Link
           ShareWare
           IMHO the best StartMenu Commodity for the AMIGA
   ToolManager
           FreeWare,
           IMHO the most important Commodity for the AMIGA
   SimpleFind 1.8 © 1998 Sebastian Bauer
           FreeWare,
           IMHO the best Filefinder yet available for the AMIGA
   CDVoyager 1996 by Luigi Catuogno
           FreeWare for Aminet CD browsing and similar tasks
           which provides Script-Plugin usability.
   Perhaps you would even find it valuable to enhance
           Directory Opus in some ways (if you would prefer
           EASys! to be your favourite FileManager, you're
           welcome!)


   I think, that even Directory Opus may lack a variety of EASys!
   functionalities, so you're invited to integrate EASys! into Opus
   as well! But, by means of EASys!, I intended primarily to rise
   significantly the comfort of the standard Workbench or of SCALOS.


   @{b}In combination with EASys!@{ub}, you may rise the comfort of
   all applications which allow to enhance their functionality
   by means of Shell-commandline entries or ARexx-Script entries,
   including argument passing to the entries.

   @{b}Please note:@{ub} Directory Opus and lots of other commodities
   are not able to interprete the EASys!-Referenes ${RefTable/...}
   because they lack a standard system shell parsing even
   for so called Shell Preferences entries. In order to enhance them
   by EASys! functionalities, please, insert the contents of the
   respective EASys! Reference directly. But keep in mind that
   such configurations will not notice center EASys! reference
   changes, such as this is the case for ToolManager, ScreenTab,
   YAM, ...



___________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node presentate "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Presentator..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________



   @{b}comfortably presentating@{ub} files of various types
   (best placed on the Dock, rShift-F4)

   @{" + " SYSTEM "run <>NIL: ${RefTable/File-Presentate}"} The EASys! Presentator: @{i}${RefTable/File-Presentate}@{ui}


   Each filetype may be totally user-specified to be
   presentated with the preferred tool/application.
   In combination with ToolManager fully Drag&Drop ability
   while still serving as Hotkey-available Presentator.

   Filetype recognition is done by the included Freeware-
   Utility "IDer" and is completely preconfigured in the 
   transparent @{"   " link philosophy} EASys!-RefTable philosophy:

   @{"   " link ENV:ider.prefs/main} ENV:IDer.prefs  will supply

   exclusively the appropriate links to the
   EASys!-Wizards. The IDer.prefs configuration file is ASCII edited
   and is already preconfigured extensively, thus it is not needed
   to make changes to that file by the user.


   If a Filetype is unknown to the presentator, it will
   automatically launch the @{"   " link EASys!_FileStarter.guide/main} EASys! FileStarter. There you
   will be able to choose interactively the appropriate
   Tool or Application for the File (the File-Starter is
   only included with the EASys! Package.

____________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node aminetcds "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Aminet-CDROMs..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}comfortably testing Aminet-CD-Archives@{ub}

   (only usable with the EASys! CompressManager which is
   available with the registered Version)

   Ever went crazy when wanting Aminet-CD MPEGs to be presentated by
   OSIRIS or ISIS... when wanting to play different modules with
   different Module-Players... when wanting to show different Picture-
   Types with different Viewers ?

   -> Just redirect the Aminet-CD's Filestarter by a Shell-Alias to
   the IDer, (Shell-Alias called while booting e.g.):

   alias AMINET21:Tools/Inspect run >NIL: EASys!_bin:IDer Aminet21:Aminet/[]
   alias AMINET22:Tools/Inspect run >NIL: EASys!_bin:IDer Aminet21:Aminet/[]
   ... (included with EASys!:
        after rebooting your system when having completed the EASys!-Base,
        intallation,  all Aminet-CDs up to number 30 are readily
        preconfigured by this kind of aliases;
        @{"   " link SYS:StartSys/b_GUI/7_StartShell/main} see SYS:StartSys/b_GUI/7_StartShell )

   then every click in the Aminet-Guides will
   automatically unpack the underlying archive to a prespecified
   Directory ( RAM:test ), thereafter you will be prompted which
   files of the unpacked data (Pictures/Sounds/Mods...) should be
   presentated in place (by the @{"   " link presentate} EASys! PresentationManager).

   After completing the testing-job everything is going to be
   cleaned up automatically. The @{"   " link presentate} IDer is included with the package.


____________________________________________________________________
@endnode


@node backupmanager "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Backups..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}Fully customizable and talking(!) AmigaDOS-based
   @{" + " SYSTEM "run <>NIL: ${RefTable/BackupManager}"} BackupManager@{ub}: @{i}${RefTable/BackupManager}@{ui}

   (included with the EASys!_Plus package)

   for incremental or complete Backups of Partitions or even
   parts (files, directories) of them. Just predefine your
   Config-Files once, then choose the desired Config by
   FileRequester and the Backup (e.g. to a Syquest 270MB
   Cartridge) will be completed. Each Backup-Partition will
   be supplied with a customizable Icon and IconPosition.

   All functions GUI-driven.
   I don't use any other BackupTools anymore since I've
   coded the EASys! Backup-Manager. It's most intuitive and
   easiest in use. Perhaps it is not as fast as others but
   you've got a multitasking Amiga, just do other nice things
   while the Backup is working!

   And, other BackupTools provide
   an own FileSystem, thus the data could easily get totally lost
   if there appears an error on the Backup Medium. As opposed
   to this kind of Backup: The Data are simply copied to a
   preformatted AmigaDOS-Partition (Syquest, e.g.).

   The advantages are clear:

       * Better protection against Data-Loss
       * You may access all data directly, whith means of daily
         work, such as the EASys! FileManager, other FileManagers,
         Workbench, DirOpus ...
       * The Backup (e.g., one of the SYS: Partition) may be used
         as a 100% Emergency-Boot-System, if your System-Harddisk
         should be striking.

   The EASys! Backup-Manager will rimind you by the
   decent female voice when it has completed it's work. EASys!!
   (as far as you have configured EASys! to talk).

____________________________________________________________________
@endnode

